# RIASEC Career Affinity Codes

The platform's career affinity quiz outputs 1–3 letter codes derived from Holland's RIASEC occupational typology.

| Letter | Type | Meaning |
|---|---|---|
| R | Realistic | Hands-on, mechanical, physical work |
| I | Investigative | Analytical, scientific, research-oriented |
| A | Artistic | Creative, expressive, unstructured |
| S | Social | Helping, teaching, interpersonal |
| E | Enterprising | Leading, persuading, business |
| C | Conventional | Organized, detail-oriented, data management |

## In-Platform Usage

- Stored in `affinity_result` field (e.g. `ISC`, `RIA`, `EC`).
- Populated for only 13.2% of sessions — quiz completion is a funnel drop-off point.
- Results correlate with [[entities/platform-career-guidance-app]] personality archetypes (e.g. Budak Skema likely maps to I/C; Otak Bisnes to E; Berdarah Seni to A).
- Dominant first-letter across completers is **I** (Investigative), consistent with a student demographic exploring academic/career paths.
